---
By: Sathya Sai Baba
Source:
  ID: 57c5499b-c3b2-4b09-92a9-a6e977a32050
  Locus:
    Page: 367
    Verse: 12
Tags:
  - Possessions
---
Do not cultivate too much attachment to things of the world, which appeal
to carnal desires and sensual thirsts. A moment comes when you have to
depart empty-handed, leaving all you have laboriously collected and proudly
called your own.
